						               													<description>milliarium is an abstract-strategy board game for 2 players, competing to be the first to build a stack of 4 blocks of their color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents&amp;#10;24 pieces, 1 board game, 1 Rule book.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Setup&amp;#10;Each player receive 12 components of the same color. Place the board in the center of the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players turn&amp;#10;At every turn you can do one of the following steps:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Place one component on the board.&amp;#10;     Move your component/stack that contains only your components, that already on the board,  1 tile in any direction in a straight line or diagonally.&amp;#10;     Step-up on 1  level on any component on the board.&amp;#10;     Step-down 1 level.&amp;#10;     Move your component on another component at the same level.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Wining  conditions&amp;#10;To be the first to build a stack of 4 blocks of your color, or when one of the players don't have any moves to do.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Notes&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     You can't move from one border to another.&amp;#10;     You can only move one level up or down. Example: component in level 2, can step-up to level 3 but not to level 4.&amp;#10;     If you need, It is allowed to stack more than 4 level.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
